From c2df85b3eb9870cc106cd1eeb4ac4abb0bf7a7e4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mingcong Bai <jeffbai@aosc.io>
Date: Sun, 4 Jan 2026 16:33:27 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] AOSCOS: fix(libsecret/meson.build): do not check system
 pkg-config

When a previous verison of libsecret is installed on the system, valac
would fail to generate VALA bindings due to incompatible API, as valac
references system pkg-config configurations.

Disallow valac from referencing pkg-config to fix build.

Link: https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/libsecret/-/issues/109

Suggested-by: Xi Ruoyao <xry111@xry111.site>
Signed-off-by: Mingcong Bai <jeffbai@aosc.io>
---
 libsecret/meson.build | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/libsecret/meson.build b/libsecret/meson.build
index 3c534d0..9dce4e6 100644
--- a/libsecret/meson.build
+++ b/libsecret/meson.build
@@ -337,6 +337,7 @@ if get_option('introspection')
         link_with: mock_service_lib,
         include_directories: config_h_dir,
         c_args: test_cflags + extra_cflags,
+        vala_args: ['--pkg-config=false'],
       )
 
       test(name, test_bin, suite: 'vala',
-- 
2.52.0

